div.p:
The main points of the note are:
—talks would be limited to the four powers and would concern West Berlin;
—the question must be approached from the standpoint of European security, and the sovereignty and legitimate interests of East Germany;
—it is impossible not to take into account that West Berlin’s lines of communication are “along the lines of communication of the GDR”;
—a normalization of relations between the GDR and Bonn proceed from the basis of “international law,” and the principles of the Bucharest and Budapest declarations of the Warsaw Pact (i.e., recognition of East Germany, inviolability of borders, etc.).See footnote 5, Document 24.
